2. RESTRICTION ON USE BY AGENTS OF BARBARIAN STATES

   This license does NOT grant any rights to the following parties, who are
   expressly prohibited from using, copying, modifying, or distributing this
   Software:

   (a) Any government, government agency, military branch, intelligence
       service, law enforcement body, or state-owned enterprise of a
       Barbarian State, as defined below;

   (b) Any individual acting in their official capacity as an agent,
       employee, contractor, or representative of such a government or
       entity;

   (c) Any organization or entity that is directly controlled by, funded
       primarily by, or operating under the direction of a Barbarian State
       government.

   For the avoidance of doubt, this restriction applies to official
   government use and agents acting in their governmental capacity. It does
   NOT restrict private citizens, residents, or nationals of any country
   acting in their personal or private professional capacity.

3. DEFINITION OF BARBARIAN STATE

   A "Barbarian State" is any state or governing regime that:

   (a) Is not a liberal democracy, defined as a system of government in
       which political power is derived from free and fair elections with
       universal suffrage, an independent judiciary, constitutional
       protections for individual rights including free expression and free
       press, and peaceful transfer of power; OR

   (b) Is actively engaged in the suppression of fundamental human rights
       as recognized by the Universal Declaration of Human Rights,
       including but not limited to: systematic persecution of ethnic,
       religious, or political minorities; extrajudicial killings;
       apartheid or ethnic cleansing; suppression of free press or free
       expression through state violence; OR

   (c) Is a regime that has seized or maintains power through the
       subversion of democratic institutions, even within a nominally
       democratic state, including through hostile foreign occupation,
       unconstitutional seizure of judicial or legislative independence,
       or systematic disenfranchisement of voters.

   The determination of whether a state qualifies as a Barbarian State
   shall be made by reference to credible international human rights
   assessments, including but not limited to reports by Freedom House,
   Reporters Without Borders, Human Rights Watch, and Amnesty International.

4. BROAD PERMISSIONS FOR THOSE OPPOSING BARBARIAN STATES

   Notwithstanding Section 2, this license grants additional broad
   permissions to any individual or organization that is actively working
   to resist, reform, dismantle, or replace a Barbarian State regime through
   lawful and nonviolent means, including but not limited to: journalists,
   human rights defenders, pro-democracy activists, civil society
   organizations, and humanitarian aid organizations — provided that such
   individual or organization is not itself an agent of a Barbarian State
   as defined in Section 2.

